               <p>THOMAS FARRANT. I saw a gentleman, who gave his name as Robert Allen, standing at the corner of <placeName id="t18310512-161-crimeloc941">Oxford-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18310512-161-crimeloc941" type="placeName" value="Oxford-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18310512-161-crimeloc941" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310512-161-off939 t18310512-161-crimeloc941"></join> - the prisoner and another boy went behind him; the other took this handkerchief out of the gentleman's pocket, and gave it to the prisoner; I made a grasp at them - I took the other, and gave him to the gentleman; the prisoner got away - I pursued, and took him in Crown-street, but he had thrown the handkerchief away; - the gentleman has now gone to Scotland.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was coming from work - the handkerchief was thrown to me, and I ran away.</p>
               <p>The prisoner received a good character.</p>
